text: Paranoá Esporte Clube, commonly known as Paranoá, is a Brazilian football club based in Paranoá, Distrito Federal. They competed in the Série C in once. ==History== The club was founded on April 4, 2000. Paranoá won the Campeonato Brasiliense Second Level in 2004. They competed in the Série C in 2005, when they were eliminated in the Second Stage by Londrina. ==Achievements== * Campeonato Brasiliense Second Level: ** Winners (1): 2004 ==Stadium== Paranoá Esporte Clube play their home games at Estádio JK Paranoá, nicknamed Estádio JK. The stadium has a maximum capacity of 6,000 people. ==References== Category:Association football clubs established in 2000 Category:Football clubs in Federal District (Brazil) Category:2000 establishments in Brazil
